readByteArray

public void readByteArray(byte[] arr,
                          int offset)
Read a string from buffer upto null character (if exists) or buffer size whichever comes first. Must take into account the text encoding defined in the Encoding Object ID3 Text Frames often allow multiple strings seperated by the null char appropriate for the encoding.

public byte[] writeByteArray()
Write String into Buffer. We need to take into account whether there are characters that require the encoding to be done using one of the UTF-16 variants. And null terminate the String.
